Lvl 12 -> 13

Goal: The password for the next level is stored in the file data.txt, which is a hexdump of a file that has been repeatedly compressed. For this level it may be useful to create a directory under /tmp in which you can work. Use mkdir with a hard to guess directory name. Or better, use the command “mktemp -d”. Then copy the datafile using cp, and rename it using mv (read the manpages!)

Command used:

cd /tmp
mktemp -d
cd /tmp/tmp.W5t1vua6G9 (usually it's random)
cp ~/data.txt .
mv data.txt hex_data

cat hex_data | head

xxd -r hex_data c_data
mv c_data c_data.gz
gzip -d c_data.gz

xxd compressed_data

mv c_data c_data.bz2
bzip2 -d c_data.bz2
mv c_data c_data.gz
gzip -d c_data.gz

cat compressed_data 

mv c_data c_data.tar
tar -xf c_data.tar
tar -xf data5.bin

xxd data6.bin

bzip2 -d data6.bin
tar -xf data6.bin.out
xxd data8.bin
mv data8.bin data8.gz
cat data8

//

xxd -r → Reverse hexdump back to binary.
file → Identify file type.
gzip, gzip2, tar -xf → Extract compressed files.

